    "text": "Ten QTL for bruchid resistance were identified on chromosomes Vu02, Vu03, Vu04, Vu06, Vu08, Vu09, and Vu11. Two major QTLs were mapped: MDP6.1(MW) on Vu06 for median development period (R-2 = 25.9%), and a co-localized QTL region on Vu09 containing NEI9.1(MW) for adult bruchid emergence number (R-2 = 28.6%), NE9.1(MW) for egg number per 10 seeds (R-2 = 18.8%), ANH9.1(MW) for average exit holes on seeds (R-2 = 19.6%), and seed weight (R-2 = 15.6%-16.3%). Markers linked to these QTLs (MDP6.1(MW), NEI9.1(MW), ANH9.1(MW)) can be validated for marker-assisted selection in cowpea breeding.",
